Nate Strand is a great tax attorney. My experience with him was pleasant. Nate is very helpful and honest. He is very attuned to your needs. He will explain the process and walk you through it. You will be so appreciative of what Nate can do. I fully recommend Nate as your tax attorney.

Thank you Nate for your great service. I look forward to recommending him to anyone in need of a tax attorney.

originalText.text: There is no one as superb, intelligent, thoughtful and competent and caring as Nate Strand. I have been through the ringer over the last years with various people in the field and it’s been a nightmare. Then I found Nate who has been compassionate, patient and excellent at helping me. I wholeheartedly recommend him to everyone. He is a gift. Thank you.

originalText.text: I ran into some complicated issues when helping my mother with her taxes. I found Nate through his online reviews and reached out and am so glad I did! He is incredibly responsive and knowledgable. Until Nate, I had dealt with a series of professionals who gave me conflicting or vague answers and I felt confused and anxious. Nate cut through the confusion and helped me find answers, with a competence and kindness that is truly unique. He also has a great sense of humor, which reduced my anxiety around dealing with the IRS and which I appreciated immensely. It's been a joy to work with Nate. I would give him more than 5 stars if I could!

originalText.text:
Nate Strand is by far the most nightmarish, frustrating experience I’ve ever had with anyone in customer service. We chose to go with him based on the positive google reviews, and our experience was a comedy of errors from the start. While Nate initially comes across as friendly over email, his tone quickly shifted to evasive and incompetent as we literally ended up having to exchange hundreds of emails due to the shocking number of errors in his work (Side note: Never trust a professional who sends you emojis in response to direct questions, and refuses to get on a call with you to run through the numbers).

A few examples of how disastrous our interactions were:
1. After sending our W-2s to Nate, he quickly generated a return which looked very different to our previous years (despite no other change to our financial situation). When I inquired about the discrepancy, he was unable to answer and just said “it’s happening to everyone”. This was blatantly untrue, as we later discovered.
2. He was unable to provide any proof of filing and when pressed, revealed significant issues of version control in submitting older, incorrect versions of the tax returns.
3. He made multiple, basic mistakes with our SSNs and omitted one full-time income on the original filing.
4. He made grave, substantial errors with our tax situation, including picking the wrong deduction and ‘forgetting’ to include key taxes paid as NYC residents.

After many months of back and forth in which we basically had to review our tax forms line by line, redo and refile our taxes ourselves, Nate refunded our fee. We will never get the time and frustration back from this experience, and I am concerned we will be dealing with the IRS/NYS for years as a result of this fiasco. He should be reported for gross incompetence and negligence. Do NOT trust your taxes with this guy!
